frameDefinitions: In this frame a group of Individuals intentionally come together to form a Group.
A Cause, animate or inanimate, causes a process, the Effect, to begin.
A perceptible Figure shows up against a Ground location due to Light shining on/from it, its salience possibly dependent on a Cause_of_shine.
A Cause leads to the formation of a Created_entity.
The Creator creates a new entity, the Created_entity, possibly out of Components.
frameExamples: We <t>assembled</t> in the courtyard to talk about our future plans.
The murder of Sergei Kirov <t>set off</t> a chain of events that culminated in the Great Terror of the 1930s.
The Libyans were <t>generating</t> arms for export.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Individuals</fen> are self-movers who intentionally assemble together.
The <fen>Group</fen> describes the resulting formation of the <fen>Individuals</fen>.

<fen>Party_1</fen> is the grammatically more prominent participant in the assembling event.  It can refer to either a single individual or a larger party separate from <fen>Party_2</fen> previous to the assembling.
A grammatically less prominent participant in the assembling event.  It can refer to either a single individual or a larger party separate from <fen>Party_1</fen> previous to the assembling.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the assembling occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the assembling occurs.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces an effect. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate the process that the <fen>Cause</fen> initiates.
This role is for the <fen>Time</fen>  when causing to start occurs
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Effect</fen> occurs.
The percept which is perceived at a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location.
The location of the phenomenon.
The <fen>Light</fen> which is emitted.  In this frame, it is usually incorporated in verbs and adjectives, and is the denotation of many of the nouns.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Figure</fen> is observed against the <fen>Ground</fen> location due to <fen>Light</fen> shining on it.
The spatial setting in which the <fen>Figure</fen> shows up against a <fen>Ground</fen> location.
A force, process, or event that produces an effect.
Agents in a joint or reciprocal action (e.g. exchange)
A positive or negative evaluation of the Phenomenon.
An entity which participates in a <fen>Cause</fen>, perhaps volitionally and perhaps not.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
This role identifies the entity that the Agent intentionally creates.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces an effect. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
The <fen>Creator</fen> creates a created entity.
This role identifes the Time when an Agent intentionally creates a new entity.
This role identifies the place ehere the Agent intentionally creates the new entity.
The Creator creates a created entity.
This role identifies the entity that the Agent intentionally creates.
This role identifes the Time when an Agent intentionally creates a new entity.
This role identifies the place ehere the Agent intentionally creates the new entity.
listRoleExamples: Few things spark <fex>the wrath of the British</fex> like food additives.
<fex>In Obscurania</fex>, the release of the movie sparked protests.
Hot coals glowed <fex>behind the fire grate</fex>.
<fex>In the morning</fex> the grass glistened with dew
<fex>Outside</fex> something was shimmering on the shore.
<fex>That one stone</fex>, apparently, caused the avalanche that engulfed square miles of forest.
